45 Super is externally/dimensionally identical to 45 acp or 45 acp+P and is designed to be used in 45 acp semi auto pistols that have been fitted with stronger than normal recoil springs and a shock buffer, plus a couple other modifications. While you can shoot 45 SUPER out of some stock 45 acp+P pistols such as the Glock 21, HK USP or the full sized all steel 1911, you will batter your pistol if you do not have them modified to handle the extra pressure and slide velocity of the 45 Super.


To learn about the modifications your 45 acp pistol needs to reliably and safely fire 45 SUPER, contact Garey Hindman at REDACTED. Garey is the foremost authority on 45 Super modifications/conversions for your 45 acp and Garey performs such conversions for a living.

5. Item # 45S255-----------1090 fps  (HARD CAST-FLAT NOSE)

 As always with Buffalo Bore Ammunition, we use real world firearms to give you real world data and results.

All our 45 Super ammunition is loaded with flash suppressed powders so that if you have to fire in low light (when the criminal element is out) you will not be blinded by your own gun fire at the worst possible moment.


All three of the JHP loads were designed for anti-personel use and for hunting small big game like deer. title: For Sale:  Brand new and never used Military Issue Launched Grapnel Hook (LGH)
location: Near Dover NH, New Hampshire, United States
postcontent:
This is a brand new in waterproof case U.S. Army issue "Launched Grapnel Hook."  Yes, it's spelled Grapnel.  It comes with several hundred feet of twine and you place it on the muzzle of a 5.56mm AR-15 / M4 and fire either a live M855 ball round or a blank (either a M195 or M200 blank) round.  

The force of the projectile or the gas from the blank shoots the LGH up to 100 meters.  According to the instructions, it can only be shot once with a live ball round, or as many times as you want with a blank round.  A live ball round sends it up to 100M with a 45 deg elevation of the rifle.  A M195 blank round sends it up to 100M and a M200 blank round sends it up to 25 meters.  (The M200 blank is the standard blank round that is used with a BFA for training.)  

I have no idea where you can get M195 blanks, but M200 blanks are easily obtained.  Further, the instructions state that if you fire the hook with a live ball round, you can still fire it later, but only with blanks.  So in other words you can never fire it more than once with live rounds or you run the risk of the hook exploding and causing death or bodily injury to the shooter or people in the area.  

This Grapnel hook is NOT for rappelling!  It's specific use is to fire it and then retrieve it, dragging it along the ground to set off tripwires.   It can also be used as a "leader" line to shoot over an obstacle and then attach a rappel line to the end and pull the rappel rope over the obstacle.  Again, DO NOT use the twine that is included or the Grapnel hook to bear weight or to climb as it will break.  Lastly, and consider this a disclaimer, firing the Grapnel hook at a person will cause death or serious bodily injury, and is also capable of damaging or destroying property.  

Email me with any questions.  I generally only accept payment with PayPal.

title: For Sale:  Military issued Israeli Mossad Tanfoglio 9mm pistol / CZ75
postcontent:
Nice MOSSAD marked 9mm Tanfoglio pistol. For those who aren't familiar with these, they were made in the same valley as Beretta in Italy by Tanfoglio, but these pistols were made for the Israeli military under contract and thus have "MOSSAD" with two 6 point "Star of David" on the slide.   This classic pistol is based upon the classic loved CZ-75 design.  Frame says "Made by Fratelli Tanfoglio S.P.A. for "Weapons House LTD" - Israel".   Bore/barrel look good, no pitting and good distinct grooves, 9mm 16 round mag double stack. One Italian made mag included. title: For Sale:  H&K .40 USP Compact Pistol
location: Stemmons Frwy and Empire Central, Dallas, Texas
postcontent:
Originally designed for the American market, the USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) has found international acceptance as an accurate and ultra-reliable handgun. Features favored by U.S. law enforcement and military users provided much of the design criteria for the USP. The controls are uniquely American, influenced by such famous designs as the Government Model 1911 pistol.

All USPs use a fiber-reinforced polymer frame stiffened by stainless steel inserts at areas subject to stress and friction. HK pioneered this use of polymer materials in the production of handguns more than 30 years ago with the development of the VP70Z and P9S pistols.

The USP control lever, a combination safety and decocking lever, is frame mounted and quickly accessible, unlike the slide-mounted safeties common on many semi-automatic pistols.

Using a modified Browning-type action with a special patented recoil reduction system, the USP recoil reduction system reduces recoil effects on pistol components and also lowers the recoil forces felt by the shooter. This same recoil reduction system has been tested and proven in the HK Mark 23 pistol developed for the U.S. Special Operations Command. The USP recoil reduction system is insensitive to ammunition types and requires no special adjustment or maintenance. It functions effectively in all USP models.

The modular design of the USP's internal components allows the control lever function to be switched from the left to the right side of the pistol for left-handed shooters. The USP can also be converted from one type of trigger firing mode to another. This includes combination double-action and single-action (DA/SA) modes and double action only (DAO) modes.

This USP is a .40 Caliber 

Features:
Corrosion proof fiber-reinforced polymer frame
Polygonal bore profile for increased velocity, easier cleaning, and longer barrel life
Can be converted to any of nine trigger firing modes
Corrosion resistant “Hostile Environment” blued finish
Oversized trigger guard for use with gloves
One piece machined slide made from nitro-carburized steel
Universal mounting grooves for installing accessories
Ambidextrous magazine release lever
Extended slide release
Patented Lock-Out Safety device
One Clip

title: For Sale/Trade:  grip/stock stippling for wood and/or polymer grips/stocks
postcontent:
TEXTURE/STIPPLING
Would you like to add a highly functional texture to your firearm that also gives it a great custom look? I've been doing this for years, and can honestly say that there is no better, or more functional texture that can be had on firearms than a custom hand finished texture. And it can be done at a reasonable price. Price does depend on what will be done though as well as quantity.

It has to be done correctly though, I've seen lots of pictures of hand stippling that looks sloppy, and terrible.... mine looks professional, and as if it were maybe done at the factory. 

It can be done very fine, which looks the best in my opinion, or it can be done more aggressively with the use of lines instead of dots or other various patterns. I have done custom hand finished textures on polymer pistol frames, ar15 and ak grips (both pistol grips and forward vertical grips to match and then Magazines to match the two grips as well. I can also do wood rifle stocks and wood pistol grips. on wood I can do a carved stippling, or a burned stippling. I can also do a fish scale pattern commonly seen on higher end target rifles, and expensive shotguns. 

COLOR FILL----------
You will also see in my photos some examples of color fill that I've done. this is the process of filling engraved lettering and/or logos with color. this is commonly done on ar15 recievers as well as logos and lettering on pistol slides, and polymer grips and other accessories. This is purely for cosmetic purposes. Examples: red spider on spikes tactical recievers, glock slide lettering/logos, magazines, ar15 pistol grip magpul logos etc.. this can all be done in pretty much any color, and is very permanent, but can be removed if absolutely desired.

Below are some pictures of my work. click on the link below the pictures to see more examples of my work. 

http://postimg.org/my.php?gallery=2a4sqgla
